**SUSTAINABLE TECHNOLOGY ADOPTION SCORE: 68/100**

Technology Adoption: 17/25  
Innovation Leadership: 16/25  
Measurable Impact: 18/25  
Future Strategy: 11/15  
Industry Position: 6/10

Summary judgment: Omnicom Group shows meaningful, measurable progress in sustainable technology adoption (notably emissions accounting, energy-efficiency/real‑estate optimization and media-ESG tools). It has credible validated targets and useful internal and client-facing tools, but it does not (as of 2022–2025 disclosures) appear to lead the holding‑company peer group in large-scale renewable procurement, proprietary low‑carbon hardware, or breakthrough climate tech R&D. The company sits in the upper‑middle of peers: active and credible, but not the sector frontrunner on sustainable‑technology deployment.

Findings and justification (by research area)

Technology Adoption (17/25) — what specific sustainable technologies has Omnicom implemented?
- Emissions measurement & management platform: Omnicom built an internal environmental data platform and integrated a third‑party carbon calculator to track Scope 1, 2 and 3 emissions across agencies (enables standardized carbon accounting and reporting) [omnicomgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFDAu55z8QsPSfQ-3TZ5u49Xy80SkHRUrSrO1YdUsSnpZFYdTQRvHQlJizrogt6STAmE7PJYmPm4YosPhpLfNRJnQllIDGmczN3ebyF67EGHD-DryzhJcNSsGCWWeS286-jXRr7tzi-4a6gpKGrMDqi71M11n1jFGHTJ5qbAZRmNgdnovvC5ZRzVduJzlrC6QBZfv1O) [credera](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE8IqfhW7c4l9POXwruYVZzNJqSxV7d2e7G50e7BqfFk73KsIOwCRyI-4Nk3UiLPKEBbmOIsr0A1mdWq6ITkmwAjRnzU2R7xCWaEuQKASfZ3nliO363Z6yRghMhiFAxv7FO2-M3d6dP9qrAy0UgG_9BJZB4eehcJ3KwtAkA6qKpab_KEGpEDbS1MFFt5pqh6wxlv5WX3URH9papGpjCbSzFLYxvT7Vk_Trb6T9tCd8=) [illuminem](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFHguLxU4N0XRK1Qb4qgs1UWkOGYJRQ6JFlHm3IBM2LWFGUWLS9loSlbDI2HAop7LWuhndu-hWVZDvcvsi9PNx6jQSEmlnttzhOpWiYjkYETJiyEZ-QZM0Tu47WSdx4frBZgABq7PNZdZiiywbe9WhQydMSc55NTgk=).
- Renewable energy procurement efforts: Omnicom states it seeks to purchase renewable electricity from utilities where possible and is exploring onsite generation in some locations; evidence of green power purchasing exists at least in the UK managed buildings [esgtoday](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFtx_5VvqkIsRzPlzSQn3iBwhBKi00_plNV8ytsqFslFJcoHs4sElSEr6_1BLc7VnDDi2EvF284swYTM2r1WDmSQR1WaRrFt80m47rnwGo0TQqTXvtNymNE0vBGDtGBGShHmQB4wfgsRIx8ASiT5CPct2dmVa6x6hRN77u9TGcrh3mwgdqS6M_CBKCGpyVU7VzPG9EbrQ==) [q4cdn](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH2ZOmo13DChxkp4gnGroUHlwNsu1feKdBSoBNuxdhtlwiuTm_-ZXfA-E-QzhCWIlXX176hVF_sciTz7ojGZZYTwW6iKK9tMk0G_UlwPwHHRSpbfO0EtfJVUCpnEzpidAhRspoYlSWyzZncXMQMMZpE4eiTKTZZwHb70X9q-P0MLJ651dkBg33VO9yH0NCm9EegrjmTJq-sjGlhBgFlBIdCIiHakAywz5wAIWeDRsaL) [omnicomgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHAWUK8jkAbnAUmS9HXFeUILsR65yA1-06-KDzNJN_1nUQOkJIBTOMS5_wCyNOWZom6rQ7QvD-1iVKiuZNqUXI5P2q4pbFOw1Gsh-OwQWTo3ki57XdeLqcN7FiZjnbV1Zb2JxKJzPsE9KfAxWNNiWZbIltL-NBSCn1-y6SsF1ian39ZWuqzAUA=).
- Energy efficiency and real estate optimization: consolidation of offices and optimization of real estate (reduced total space by ~1.1 million sq ft between 2022–2023) to reduce energy use [omnicomgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHAWUK8jkAbnAUmS9HXFeUILsR65yA1-06-KDzNJN_1nUQOkJIBTOMS5_wCyNOWZom6rQ7QvD-1iVKiuZNqUXI5P2q4pbFOw1Gsh-OwQWTo3ki57XdeLqcN7FiZjnbV1Zb2JxKJzPsE9KfAxWNNiWZbIltL-NBSCn1-y6SsF1ian39ZWuqzAUA=) [omnicomgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGQ_h7Ma2Epa-H3oDls6UGUHAl2vzdYZOYDgVp7M0Y_wvVmdOEb5_zTqZl9h7uWi5qnTBOAEVrnYFBrG4ODr3ZyvHW-EmIBQ-xsodpgaPmOI8ke_scBQd70g7tHx614NHcLxaO7cIs0g1b08ZH_79yN8Y4JnEfRvfF4gmFILjWQxyE6z1bn13M=).
- Fleet / travel management and operational efficiency: programs to manage fleet mileage and travel emissions (e.g., CPM’s UK program reduced road travel emissions by ~10% in 2023) [cpm-int](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFMRtii31uiLQNAg9yl25dYpZjKGb3xcOBCMyuUV5TaJAGSaxMAXl14_3m0is6Bd7bfLGcqkjmYAupF5sXaCiWeN5o7X-FfOihkyvmHClc12bElME0uL0Ir-x2nVAWSlzocLlzWEZe_Tb20Wgl2Ezw_HizoJpjp9PHP7dxPYmpR5ukQbbZi-4o-).
- Client / media ESG tooling: Omnicom Media Group launched OMG Impact (2023), a tool that scores media owners across ESG dimensions (12 categories) to help advertisers measure the ESG impact of media spend — an operationally useful digital tool for sustainable procurement of media [omg](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFfmK_wWtYYx4qs5u3pAbcCl5XFfHa9jz2ADLeBEHOKp0V0u_N2QV9iLVrMIJdb5uKZSYDWVcc8BHIKZ_zng5uQlGSOOFSJ8WvgCXT84B3w59WyzKOQmVQo3H63brGUNOAueWo3AQsBtgk=) [themedialeader](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEMjC30W4BNdz3Z0S4up8EWkoba0GJ_WpOZoKnDc-KNZ-nAAE3I-dVpy80kCtaYAZkjY-RnK3tMiZHJsQtIGKi1ZlZaRjwa95czu3dMOk427dUjJkNHCunBEVSCN2jokuJb8TmTTG4Bz58Ad_97jyBpHGf7QkESS0v9RsRgfI4_IEKq6PMwLNpA1X3yu87YQ2WuforhI05s) [creativebrief](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG15rcUfu8pd7iHI2WKm0EnSHZ_w5ZMK9FmqqHgCUY7Rnx0iNBRr79piLN9-A9sg76WLzEDKZsIufepJ3_wm27T6bJkzgN7chZZpt9RInqc1doRSeTtp8jG5xFOszIZQOCiR3n5sUOyUe7mP7fhhShb-QJl8YfWQwgSsGbrPA-A0GLp).
- Participation in industry initiatives: Ad Net Zero membership and UN Global Compact signatory status (industry coordination rather than proprietary tech) [lbbonline](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG3hbdqvdKSZT_1DPDmz3vdBNqW2eok_QUbhArBrCfSIOQMjT7p4IKn8uH375RSfssdZZXzTGqSUbZk8YcGSct-_k0QkyZKcjhKY0WWHVPZTVry0qBKT5_kzYHi_NGCIOKf8BnbIS8n7Ig5kr7dL1sV2kFeddaqUyw6wanKO3v02a_fJnFbIdEF6C7qBvy3dadxerJrFw==) [q4cdn](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHaOf2gqgx3FfQys6_J_lnmiufoDeYtwzvIy7qE9BXIhixIV3CadHLisMfxUoCwvFzhHgYOInCNqYjvMRID4QU3UqTPDrQATZewZw7hLAHvDbG-Uq-dMwcDkdv92JGy9PUY6ToPRzVzzRCwuGgjecFscFENWRDqI92OLy5L56JL-crR1JsX9fdSSXJwEPE-R7gbf2l2xNtT0h1fDxE6L35Jrw==).

Why 17/25: Omnicom has deployed multiple relevant technology systems (environmental data platform, carbon calculator, OMG Impact, travel/fleet programs) and is implementing renewable procurement in some markets. However, there is limited public evidence of multiple large‑scale breakthrough technologies implemented across global operations (e.g., corporate PPAs covering a large share of electricity, widescale onsite renewables, or a major fleet EV rollout). That places Omnicom above “some adoption” but short of “breakthrough technologies at scale.”

