Measurable Impact (18/25) — quantifiable environmental/business outcomes
- SBTi‑validated target and progress: Omnicom’s near‑term target (absolute reduction of Scope 1, 2 and 3 emissions by 46.2% by 2030 vs 2019) was validated by the Science Based Targets initiative in 2023; Omnicom reported a 30.2% reduction in combined Scope 1, 2 and 3 emissions as of 2023 vs 2019 baseline — a substantial, measurable improvement [omnicomgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH619wFHBtb2zuqz-uD-nCmfV1XrTIMAJlB4iZ23Pv0yXkixAfkYDfwmNqU0KEWfLotA-DPd05OtYSLaHG7OgafGkKnHRhY-EPhaciihlMOCDKalC8Nh4QtwNrJylDVxjJ0mXDFqam2bxzCfHEVdOPlMgTodJy-wQaCcRXVm5w0oWR0_bzyTugbzoop6u5yduuHC0tv) [illuminem](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFV-YIFuhIlJ4OWVD_GUaaQJ-KOTCIsIIvwqH8CrKWOrsWMh6bN1TQS7J9A7fF_h7cOUwnWZ-aYWAn45v_aLEwLlXOj19GxuCYUfNdyAoirE1xMSKw4tK5VrE-CGuhA_hdofBUzzvToT9nvZOVF8M-dzQc8tr5oX9c=) [omnicomgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFDAu55z8QsPSfQ-3TZ5u49Xy80SkHRUrSrO1YdUsSnpZFYdTQRvHQlJizrogt6STAmE7PJYmPm4YosPhpLfNRJnQllIDGmczN3ebyF67EGHD-DryzhJcNSsGCWWeS286-jXRr7tzi-4a6gpKGrMDqi71M11n1jFGHTJ5qbAZRmNgdnovvC5ZRzVduJzlrC6QBZfv1O).
- Detailed 2022→2023 trends: Omnicom reports Scope 1 rose 18% (fleet mileage and DEFRA factor changes), Scope 2 flat, Scope 3 up 3% (business travel increases) — indicating some headwinds and the areas to target next [omnicomgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGEvoWeY-yq1gUr9nSqLfn1GFkCbrk40CAbt33pkS2MW0QAuJCWo38Hkqhnpb89Ar2DKqnX0ur-p4GOKrMPbf6lZI3YRnD8B5HhUJuxQrBxnA-ky_OJlgaJXb58djIAdLaGpkiTn_veW1IjO70oqFv_OGKpTKBDh6Sek-TdO9OJdneypSeIwSphpUnNe26KUXiZqaqD) [omnicomgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQExwQrY1uuIjm_vbWIjOS62_GQDtlHA5M4ZcTcG-yGCz4KpOIiJFAyX1NiPSjy3RQfRf3mqwgPd99LZb0QKzcI5eYynu3uOSQuA0KcFRYjVFqDUDSsJ5Gv7NhnZgPGJPp7WpW8lucJFI15uFyaY7dh1dl86I1CvG44MUT9lhW_Bbm5QhUoZP6ciNlhRGAWI7oIYmdRE).
- Operational metrics: office space reduced by ~1.1 million sq ft (2022–2023), which supports lower energy use; CPM reported a 10% drop in road travel emissions in the UK in 2023 after operational efforts [omnicomgroup](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHAWUK8jkAbnAUmS9HXFeUILsR65yA1-06-KDzNJN_1nUQOkJIBTOMS5_wCyNOWZom6rQ7QvD-1iVKiuZNqUXI5P2q4pbFOw1Gsh-OwQWTo3ki57XdeLqcN7FiZjnbV1Zb2JxKJzPsE9KfAxWNNiWZbIltL-NBSCn1-y6SsF1ian39ZWuqzAUA=) [cpm-int](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFMRtii31uiLQNAg9yl25dYpZjKGb3xcOBCMyuUV5TaJAGSaxMAXl14_3m0is6Bd7bfLGcqkjmYAupF5sXaCiWeN5o7X-FfOihkyvmHClc12bElME0uL0Ir-x2nVAWSlzocLlzWEZe_Tb20Wgl2Ezw_HizoJpjp9PHP7dxPYmpR5ukQbbZi-4o-).

Why 18/25: The 30.2% reduction since 2019 is a strong, verifiable improvement (squarely in the 25–50% band), and Omnicom has credible measurement systems. However, the recent year‑on‑year rise in Scope 1 and the small rise in Scope 3 highlight incomplete progress in some operational areas; Omnicom’s impact is notable but not yet at the >50% / transformative level.

